ment variable, or system property is indicated. OSGi coverage can be exercised with in-process BundleContext/Bundle/ServiceReference test doubles; a real OSGi container is not required for meaningful unit-level coverage.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If the generated build also keeps org.osgi:osgi_R4_core:1.0, it provides older duplicate org.osgi.framework classes but not BundleReference; local Gradle verification should confirm classpath ordering does not mask the 4.2.0 API jar.\",\n    \"jersey-core also declares javax.mail:mail and javax.xml.bind:jaxb-api as provided dependencies; existing scaffold already includes them, but newly generated tests that exercise mail or JAXB providers still depend on those APIs being present.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c4854261b577613016a42a7ba67ac8194b8db3d213d76269d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 676, "output": 1190, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29514, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782753192467, "responseId": "resp_0c4854261b577613016a42a7a8f5b08194bfda37a56b872016"}}
